*Department of Systems Engineering and Operations Research*\n
*George Mason University*\n
*Fall 2017*\n

#* For Syllabus click [syllabus.html here]*\n


The class will consist of 7-8 lectures given by the instructor on several advanced topics in data analysis. The rest of the semester (another 6-7 lectures) students will present on the topic of their choice. 

* For Lecture notes and homework click [https://www.dropbox.com/sh/q2ywfjg4rj569c0/AAClairRwV4p6mINUiA1O_nSa?dl=0 here]*\n

== Course Presentations
- Bayesian Optimization for ML and Engineering. By Laura Schultz (11/1)
- Adversarial Auto-encoders. By Bill Jeffries on 11/8
- RNN for EDU: [https://web.stanford.edu/~cpiech/bio/papers/deepKnowledgeTracing.pdf Deep Knowledge Tracing]. By Qian Hu (11/8)
- RNN/LSTM. By Darron Fuller.
- Hierarchical Bayes and STAN. By Tuan Lee (11\/15)
- Convolutional Networks: Convolution/pooling layers, network design, theory. By Kathleen Perez-Lopez on 11\/15. Materials: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5shwqPBVpbc&index=4&list=PLkFD6_40KJIxopmdJF_CLNqG3QuDFHQUm Brief info], [https://youtu.be/4TLYJ20kniA lecture video], [https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1453965/files/69671012/download?verifier=XD3l2nlSb1lJ5CUTGcJA7YSU7Ttel1VtvyTzd28J slides]


- DL for Threat Detection. By James Lee. 11/29
- VAE: [https://arxiv.org/abs/1705.07120 VAE with a VampPrior]. By Hossein Fotouhi on 11/29.
- Language Modeling: [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1602.02410.pdf Exploring the Limits of Language Modeling], [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1301.3781.pdf Efficient Estimation of Word Representations in Vector Space], [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1405.4053.pdf Distributed Representations of Sentences and Documents]. By Anya Mityushina on 11/29
- Reinforcement learning. By Jeff Schneider


